 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# LangChain — Complex Agent\n",
    "\n",
    "**Framework:** LangChain (LCEL)  \n",
    "**Level:** 03 — Complex  \n",
    "**Model:** `gemini-2.0-flash`\n",
    "\n",
    "### What's New vs Intermediate\n",
    "| Feature | Intermediate | Complex |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| Structure | Single chain | **4 chained chains** (Plan → Execute → Critique → Revise) |\n",
    "| Pattern | Tool-calling agent | **Plan-and-Execute + Reflexion** |\n",
    "| Quality control | None | **Critic chain gates the output** |\n",
    "| Streaming | None | **`.stream()` on the executor** |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Concept: Plan-and-Execute + Reflexion\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Goal Input\n",
    "    │\n",
    "    ▼\n",
    "┌──────────────────────┐\n",
    "│   Planner Chain      │  prompt | llm | StrOutputParser\n",
    "│   'Research step 1:  │  → numbered plan\n",
    "│    get Tokyo data...'│\n",
    "└──────────┬───────────┘\n",
    "           │ plan text\n",
    "           ▼\n",
    "┌──────────────────────┐\n",
    "│   Executor Agent     │  create_tool_calling_agent + AgentExecutor\n",
    "│   Runs the plan      │  → calls tools, synthesizes report\n",
    "│   step by step       │\n",
    "└──────────┬───────────┘\n",
    "           │ draft report\n",
    "           ▼\n",
    "┌──────────────────────┐\n",
    "│   Critic Chain       │  prompt | llm | StrOutputParser\n",
    "│   SCORE:8 VERDICT:   │  → structured critique\n",
    "│   PASS / REVISE      │\n",
    "└──────────┬───────────┘\n",
    "     PASS  │  REVISE\n",
    "     ─────▼│▼─────────\n",
    "          ┌┴┐\n",
    "   END ◀──┤ ├──▶ Reviser Chain ──▶ back to Critic\n",
    "          └─┘      (max 2 retries)\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key LCEL insight:** Each chain is `prompt | llm | parser`. You compose them in Python code, not inside a single prompt. This makes each step testable in isolation — you can run the Planner chain alone, inspect the plan, then feed it to the Executor."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "from dotenv import load_dotenv\n",
    "\n",
    "from langchain_google_genai import ChatGoogleGenerativeAI\n",
    "from langchain_core.tools import tool\n",
    "from langchain_core.prompts import ChatPromptTemplate, MessagesPlaceholder\n",
    "from langchain_core.output_parsers import StrOutputParser\n",
    "from langchain.agents import AgentExecutor, create_tool_calling_agent\n",
    "\n",
    "load_dotenv()\n",
    "assert os.getenv(\"GOOGLE_API_KEY\"), \"Set GOOGLE_API_KEY in your .env\"\n",
    "print(\"✓ Ready\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Tools — With Scores for Richer Comparison"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "@tool\n",
    "def get_weather(city: str) -> dict:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Return weather data including a weather score (1-10) for a city.\"\"\"\n",
    "    data = {\n",
    "        \"london\":    {\"condition\": \"Cloudy\",       \"temp_c\": 12, \"score\": 5},\n",
    "        \"new york\":  {\"condition\": \"Sunny\",         \"temp_c\": 22, \"score\": 8},\n",
    "        \"bangalore\": {\"condition\": \"Rainy\",         \"temp_c\": 25, \"score\": 6},\n",
    "        \"tokyo\":     {\"condition\": \"Clear\",         \"temp_c\": 18, \"score\": 9},\n",
    "        \"paris\":     {\"condition\": \"Partly Cloudy\", \"temp_c\": 16, \"score\": 7},\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    key = city.lower()\n",
    "    return {\"city\": city, **data[key]} if key in data else {\"error\": f\"No data.\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "@tool\n",
    "def get_time(city: str) -> dict:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Return current local time for a city.\"\"\"\n",
    "    times = {\n",
    "        \"london\": \"14:30 GMT\", \"new york\": \"09:30 EST\",\n",
    "        \"bangalore\": \"20:00 IST\", \"tokyo\": \"22:30 JST\", \"paris\": \"15:30 CET\",\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    return {\"city\": city, \"local_time\": times.get(city.lower(), \"Unknown\")}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "@tool\n",
    "def get_travel_advisory(city: str) -> dict:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Return travel safety advisory and safety score for a city.\"\"\"\n",
    "    data = {\n",
    "        \"london\":    {\"level\": \"Low\",    \"notes\": \"Routine precautions.\",      \"safety_score\": 8},\n",
    "        \"new york\":  {\"level\": \"Low\",    \"notes\": \"Normal precautions.\",       \"safety_score\": 7},\n",
    "        \"bangalore\": {\"level\": \"Medium\", \"notes\": \"Monsoon affects transport.\", \"safety_score\": 6},\n",
    "        \"tokyo\":     {\"level\": \"Low\",    \"notes\": \"Very safe city.\",            \"safety_score\": 10},\n",
    "        \"paris\":     {\"level\": \"Low\",    \"notes\": \"Alert in crowded spots.\",    \"safety_score\": 8},\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    key = city.lower()\n",
    "    return {\"city\": city, **data[key]} if key in data else {\"error\": f\"No advisory.\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "tools = [get_weather, get_time, get_travel_advisory]\n",
    "print(f\"{len(tools)} tools defined\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Chain 1: Planner\n",
    "\n",
    "A simple LLM chain — no tools needed. Just a prompt that decomposes the goal into a numbered research plan."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "llm = ChatGoogleGenerativeAI(model=\"gemini-2.0-flash\", temperature=0)\n",
    "llm_creative = ChatGoogleGenerativeAI(model=\"gemini-2.0-flash\", temperature=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "planner_prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\n",
    "    (\"system\",\n",
    "     \"You are a research planner. Given a travel comparison task, output a numbered list of \"\n",
    "     \"research steps. Each step: 'N. Research [city]: get weather, time, advisory'. Be concise.\"),\n",
    "    (\"human\", \"{goal}\"),\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "# LCEL pipe: prompt → LLM → parse to string\n",
    "planner_chain = planner_prompt | llm | StrOutputParser()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test the planner in isolation\n",
    "test_plan = planner_chain.invoke({\"goal\": \"Compare Tokyo, Paris, and Bangalore for travel.\"})\n",
    "print(\"Planner output:\")\n",
    "print(test_plan)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Chain 2: Executor Agent\n",
    "\n",
    "A tool-calling agent that receives the plan and executes it — calling tools for each city."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "executor_prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\n",
    "    (\"system\",\n",
    "     \"You are a travel research executor. You receive a research plan and execute it. \"\n",
    "     \"For each city in the plan, call get_weather, get_time, and get_travel_advisory. \"\n",
    "     \"After gathering all data, write a comprehensive comparison report with city rankings.\"),\n",
    "    (\"human\", \"Plan:\\n{plan}\\n\\nExecute this plan and write the comparison report.\"),\n",
    "    MessagesPlaceholder(\"agent_scratchpad\"),\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "executor_agent = create_tool_calling_agent(llm, tools, executor_prompt)\n",
    "executor = AgentExecutor(agent=executor_agent, tools=tools, verbose=False)\n",
    "print(\"Executor agent ready\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Chain 3: Critic\n",
    "\n",
    "A chain that scores the report and returns a structured verdict. No tools — pure LLM judgment."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "critic_prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\n",
    "    (\"system\",\n",
    "     \"You are a travel report editor. Score the report 1-10. Check: has rankings? \"\n",
    "     \"specific numbers? safety info? at least 200 chars?\\n\"\n",
    "     \"Respond ONLY in this exact format:\\n\"\n",
    "     \"SCORE:[number] VERDICT:[PASS/REVISE] ISSUES:[text or None]\"),\n",
    "    (\"human\", \"Report to evaluate:\\n\\n{report}\"),\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "critic_chain = critic_prompt | llm | StrOutputParser()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test the critic\n",
    "test_critique = critic_chain.invoke({\"report\": \"Tokyo is great.\"})\n",
    "print(\"Critic on bad draft:\", test_critique)\n",
    "\n",
    "test_critique2 = critic_chain.invoke({\"report\": (\n",
    "    \"1. Tokyo (score 9): Clear skies, 18°C. Safety: Low advisory, score 10/10. Time: 22:30 JST.\\n\"\n",
    "    \"2. Paris (score 7): Partly Cloudy, 16°C. Safety: Low advisory, score 8/10. Time: 15:30 CET.\\n\"\n",
    "    \"3. Bangalore (score 6): Rainy season, 25°C. Safety: Medium advisory, score 6/10. Time: 20:00 IST.\\n\"\n",
    "    \"Recommendation: Tokyo is the top choice for best weather and safety.\"\n",
    ")})\n",
    "print(\"Critic on good draft:\", test_critique2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Chain 4: Reviser\n",
    "\n",
    "Only invoked when the Critic says REVISE. Rewrites the report addressing specific issues."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "reviser_prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_messages([\n",
    "    (\"system\", \"You are a travel writer. Improve the report based on the critique. \"\n",
    "               \"Keep all existing data. Fix only the identified issues.\"),\n",
    "    (\"human\", \"Original report:\\n{report}\\n\\nCritique:\\n{critique}\\n\\nImproved version:\"),\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "reviser_chain = reviser_prompt | llm_creative | StrOutputParser()\n",
    "print(\"Reviser chain ready\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Orchestrator: Wiring the Chains\n",
    "\n",
    "The orchestrator is plain Python — calling each chain in sequence, with conditional logic for the reflexion loop."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def run(goal: str, max_retries: int = 2) -> str:\n",
    "    # Step 1: Plan\n",
    "    print(\"[1/4] Planning...\")\n",
    "    plan = planner_chain.invoke({\"goal\": goal})\n",
    "    print(f\"Plan:\\n{plan}\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Step 2: Execute\n",
    "    print(\"[2/4] Executing plan...\")\n",
    "    result = executor.invoke({\"plan\": plan})\n",
    "    report = result[\"output\"]\n",
    "    print(f\"Draft ({len(report)} chars)\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Steps 3+4: Critique → Revise loop\n",
    "    for attempt in range(max_retries):\n",
    "        print(f\"[3/4] Critiquing (attempt {attempt + 1}/{max_retries})...\")\n",
    "        critique = critic_chain.invoke({\"report\": report})\n",
    "        print(f\"Critique: {critique}\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "        if \"VERDICT: PASS\" in critique or \"VERDICT:PASS\" in critique:\n",
    "            print(\"[4/4] ✓ Quality check passed.\")\n",
    "            break\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            print(f\"[4/4] Revising...\")\n",
    "            report = reviser_chain.invoke({\"report\": report, \"critique\": critique})\n",
    "            print(f\"Revised ({len(report)} chars)\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    return report\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Orchestrator defined\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "goal = \"Compare Tokyo, Paris, and Bangalore for travel. I want the safest city with the best weather.\"\n",
    "final_report = run(goal)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(\"FINAL REPORT\")\n",
    "print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "print(final_report)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Streaming the executor (observe tool calls in real-time)\n",
    "print(\"--- Streaming executor for a single city ---\")\n",
    "for chunk in executor.stream({\"plan\": \"1. Research Tokyo: get weather, time, advisory\"}):\n",
    "    if \"output\" in chunk:\n",
    "        print(f\"Output chunk: {str(chunk['output'])[:100]}\")\n",
    "    elif \"intermediate_steps\" in chunk:\n",
    "        steps = chunk[\"intermediate_steps\"]\n",
    "        if steps:\n",
    "            action, result = steps[-1]\n",
    "            print(f\"Tool: {action.tool}({action.tool_input}) → {str(result)[:80]}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Key Takeaways\n",
    "\n",
    "| What You Saw | Why It Matters |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| 4 separate chains | Each is testable in isolation — debug Planner without running Executor |\n",
    "| `planner_chain = prompt \\| llm \\| parser` | LCEL pipe — cleanest chain composition syntax |\n",
    "| Critic returns structured text | Forces parseable output from the LLM for conditional logic |\n",
    "| Python loop for reflexion | Max retries are code-enforced — no risk of infinite LLM loops |\n",
    "| `.stream()` on executor | Observe tool calls without waiting for final output |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Plan-and-Execute vs ReAct\n",
    "| Pattern | How it works | Best when |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| **ReAct** (Simple/Intermediate) | LLM decides each tool call on the fly | Short, reactive tasks |\n",
    "| **Plan-and-Execute** (this notebook) | Planner writes the full plan; Executor follows it | Long tasks with multiple steps that are known upfront |\n",
    "\n",
    "### LangChain vs LangGraph at Complex Level\n",
    "- **LangChain:** reflexion loop is Python code in the orchestrator (`for attempt in range(...)`) — flexible but invisible\n",
    "- **LangGraph:** reflexion loop is a **graph edge** — explicit, inspectable, and supports streaming node transitions\n",
    "\n",
    "### Next: Compare with [LangGraph 03-Complex →](../../LangGraph/03-complex/agent.ipynb)"
   ]
  }
 ],
